A split composition showing two contrasting nighttime campus scenes in Studio Ghibli animation style: on the left, a warm amber-lit colonial Asian university courtyard with ornate traditional architecture, perfectly manicured gardens, and stern stone lion statues standing guard under a controlled, orderly moonlit sky; on the right, a chaotic New England ivy-covered quadrangle in deep winter with snow swirling wildly, gothic brick buildings with glowing windows, abandoned scarves and shoes scattered across frosted cobblestones, steam rising from breath in the frigid air. The two scenes are divided by a gentle curved line where warm tropical humidity meets cold northern frost, creating a misty boundary. Fireflies dot the Singapore side while snowflakes dance on the Cambridge side. The mood captures institutional rigidity meeting rebellious freedom, all rendered with soft watercolor textures, gentle cel shading, and that distinctive Ghibli luminosity in the night sky.
